The turkey is a large bird in the genus Meleagris, which is native to the Americas. One species, Meleagris gallopavo (commonly known as the wild turkey or domestic turkey), is native to the forests of North America, mainly Mexico and the United States.The other living species is Meleagris ocellata or the ocellated turkey, native to the forests of the Yucatan YucatÃ¡n. peninsulaeleagris redirects here. For the familiar species, see Domesticated turkey and Wild turkey. For turkey as a food, see Turkey (food) . For other uses, see Turkey (disambiguation) and Meleagris (disambiguation) .
